4 Climb - 1 Logging ascents

<p>There are a few reasons why you might want to log your ascents:</p>

<ul class="sd-checklist">
 <li>Keep a record of the routes you've done.</li>
 <li>Allow friends to follow your what you have done.</li>
 <li>Help us recommend routes for you.</li>
 <li>Used in crowd sourced guidebooks.</li>
</ul>

<p>Here's how you do it.</p>
<ul>
 <li><a href="#singleascent">Adding a tick</a></li>
 <li><a href="#multipleshots">Multiple route shots</a></li>
 <li><a href="#multipleticks">Adding multiple ticks</a></li>
 <li><a href="#pitchinfo">Adding pitch info</a></li>
 <li><a href="#firstpitch">Log first pitch only</a></li>
 <li><a href="#linkup">Log a linkup</a></li>
</ul>

<h1 id="singleascent">Adding a tick</h1>

<p>HOW TO VIDEO TO BE UPDATED</p>

<iframe title="YouTube video player" class="youtube-player" type="text/html" width="640" height="390" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/G2E5vgpS1d4?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowFullScreen></iframe>

<p>From the route page:</p>

<ol>
 <li>Click 'Log an ascent'</li>
 <li>Complete the details of your ascent</li>
 <li>Click 'Save'</li>
</ol>


<h1 id="multipleshots">Multiple shots of the same route</h1>

<p>HOW TO VIDEO TO BE COMPLETED</p>

<p>From the route page:</p>
<ol>
 <li>Click 'Log an ascent'</li>
 <li>Complete the details of your ascent</li>
 <li>For multiple shots click the 'Add shot' button.</li>
 <li>Click 'Save'</li>
 <li>(note that each shot will be saved as a separate ascent.)</li>
</ol>


<h1 id="multipleticks">Adding multiple ticks</h1>

<p>HOW TO VIDEO TO BE UPDATED</p>

<iframe title="YouTube video player" class="youtube-player" type="text/html" width="640" height="390" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/_CW968PAHA8?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowFullScreen></iframe>

<p>If you've done several routes on the one wall you can:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Check the boxes of the routes you've climbed by clicking on the route row.</li>
  <li>Click the tick icon next to the route.</li>
  <li>Complete the details of your ascents</li>
  <li>Click 'Save'</li>
</ol>


<h1 id="pitchinfo">Adding pitch info</h1>

<p>HOW TO VIDEO TO BE COMPLETED</p>

<p>From the route page:</p>
<ol>
 <li>Click 'Log an ascent'</li>
 <li>Complete the standard details of your ascent</li>
 <li>Click the 'log pitch fields' checkbox to make pitch fields appear.</li>
 <li>Complete the pitch fields and add or delete pitches as required.</li>
 <li>Click 'Save'</li>
</ol>


<h1 id="firstpitch">Log first pitch only</h1>

<p>HOW TO VIDEO TO BE COMPLETED</p>

<p>From the route page:</p>
<ol>
 <li>Click 'Log an ascent'</li>
 <li>Click the 'log pitch fields' checkbox to make pitch fields appear.</li>
 <li>Delete all but the fist pitch of the route (or set all but the first pitch numbers to blank).</li>
 <li>The form should automatically update the ascent name by adding a 'P1' to the end of the name (eg 'Bard P1').</li>
 <li>Click 'Save'</li>
 <li>(note that you can manually edit the ascent name after the ascent has been created)</li>
</ol>

<p>Note this method works for doing any single pitch of a route, not just the first pitch.</p>


<h1 id="linkup">Log a linkup</h1>

<p>HOW TO VIDEO TO BE COMPLETED</p>

<p>From the route page:</p>
<ol>
 <li>Click 'Log an ascent'</li>
 <li>Click the 'log pitch fields' checkbox to make pitch fields appear.</li>
 <li>Type in the linkup climb name in the pitch linkup field.</li>
 <li>The form should automatically update the ascent name by adding a 'Linkup xyz' to the end of the name (eg 'Bard Linkup Eurydice').</li>
 <li>Click 'Save'</li>
</ol>
